  "signature": "ed25519:b7e3a1f4c2d8059e6b3a1f4c2d8059e6b3a1f4c2d8059e6b3a1f4c2d8059e6b",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must have documented V&V test suite with regression testing and version-controlled source under a quality management system compliant with 21 CFR Part 11.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) has a documented verification test suite; however, the site-level quality management system lacks formal 21 CFR Part 11 audit trails for simulation runs, yielding achieved level 2 against the required level 4 at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal order-of-accuracy verification on canonical rotating-flow and non-Newtonian transport benchmarks demonstrating expected convergence rates.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests were performed on a lid-driven cavity and a Couette flow with power-law fluid; observed convergence rates matched theoretical expectations for velocity but deviated for scalar hemolysis transport, leaving a gap at the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for all QoIs with GCI below 5% on the hemolysis index at the design operating point.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed; GCI for velocity field is 3.1% but GCI for hemolysis index reaches 11.4% at high-speed operating point due to thin shear-layer sensitivity, placing achieved level at 3 versus required 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope including hematocrit range 35–45%, temperature 37°C ± 0.5°C, and pulsatile waveform representative of resting cardiac output.",
      "rationale": "Available FDA benchmark experiments used steady-state conditions with bovine blood at fixed hematocrit 40%; pulsatile and temperature-controlled conditions matching the clinical VAD envelope were not tested, resulting in achieved level 2 against the required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or validation metric M_v) computed for hemolysis index QoI with uncertainty bounds; metric must demonstrate agreement within ±15% at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Relative error on hemolysis index ranges from 18% to 47% across the five operating points; systematic over-prediction at high flow rates indicates model-form inadequacy in the hemolysis power-law exponent, achieving only level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress exposure time) must be validated independently.",
      "rationale": "NIH is directly mapped to the clinical hemolysis threshold; shear stress exposure time is computed but not independently validated against experimental Lagrangian particle tracking, limiting the achieved level to 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties representative of the target VAD COU; extrapolation distance must be formally quantified.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry under steady-state conditions; the target VAD geometry differs in impeller blade angle and diffuser design, and pulsatile operation introduces significant extrapolation distance not formally quantified, yielding achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Round-off and iterative convergence errors must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was monitored via residual drop to 1e-5 but no formal round-off or floating-point error analysis was conducted; this factor was flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5 and remains not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented evidence that simulation setup (boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, meshing strategy) was reviewed by an independent analyst following a formal checklist.",
      "rationale": "No independent analyst review of simulation setup was performed; the single analyst who built and ran the model also performed the post-processing, creating an unquantified use-error risk that leaves this factor not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal model-form uncertainty analysis comparing at least two turbulence closure models and two hemolysis damage accumulation models with quantified contribution to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Only the k-omega SST turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model were used; no model-form comparison or formal model-form uncertainty quantification was attempted, leaving this factor not-assessed at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients, inlet velocity profile) must have assigned probability distributions derived from experimental characterization; Monte Carlo propagation must report 90% credible intervals on all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated using nominal literature distributions for hemolysis model coefficients; however, viscosity and inlet profile uncertainties were not characterized, and the Monte Carlo run was terminated early due to computational cost, leaving this factor not-assessed. A screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank parameter influence but did not yield the full probabilistic characterization required at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used for validation must be fully characterized for material properties and geometric tolerances; inter-sample variability must be reported and propagated into validation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark dataset does not include inter-sample variability data for the blood analogue fluid or geometric tolerances of the test pump; this information was not available and the factor is flagged as not-assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between validation test input parameters and COU input parameters must demonstrate equivalency or bound the extrapolation; differences in Reynolds number, hematocrit, and rotational speed must be explicitly addressed.",
      "rationale": "The validation dataset operates at Reynolds numbers and hematocrit values that differ from the target VAD COU; no formal equivalency analysis or extrapolation bounding was performed, leaving this factor not-assessed at MRL 5."
    }
